This Java code builds a singly linked list with nodes containing values 5, 10, and 15, then prints them in order. It starts by creating node a (data=10) and setting head to point to a. Then node b (data=15) is created and linked as a.next = b, forming the list 10 → 15. Next, node c (data=5) is created with its next pointing to a using the parameterized constructor new Node(5, a), and head is updated to point to c, resulting in the list 5 → 10 → 15. Finally, the code traverses from head using a while loop, printing each node's data, which outputs: 5 10 15.

import java.util.*;

class Node {
  int data;
  Node next;
  public Node(int data, Node next){
      this.data = data;
      this.next = next;
  }
  public Node(int data){
      this.data = data;
      this.next = null;
  }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
      Node a = new Node(10);
      Node head = a;
      Node b = new Node(15);
      a.next = b;
      Node c = new Node(5, a);
      head = c;
      Node temp = head;
        while (temp != null) {
            System.out.print(temp.data + " ");
            temp = temp.next;
        }
    }
}
